### Test API Endpoints
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@superadminToken = 
@adminToken = 

### 1. Login as Superadmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "superadmin@losia.com",
  "password": "superadmin123"
}

### 2. Get current user info (Superadmin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{superadminToken}}

### 3. Create Admin user (Only Superadmin can do this - SUPERADMIN level 100 > ADMIN level 50)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{superadminToken}}

{
  "email": "admin@losia.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "firstName": "Admin",
  "lastName": "User",
  "role": "ADMIN",
  "level": 50
}

###
# Level Constants Reference:
# SUPERADMIN: 100
# ADMIN: 50
# MANAGER: 30
# STAFF: 10
# USER: 0

### 4. Login as Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@losia.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 5. Try to create another Admin (Should FAIL - ADMIN level 50 cannot create level 50)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "email": "admin2@losia.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "firstName": "Admin",
  "lastName": "Two",
  "role": "ADMIN",
  "level": 50
}

